# Project card preview images

When **adding or duplicating** a `ProjectEntry` in [`Pages/Projects.cshtml.cs`](Pages/Projects.cshtml.cs), **ask the user for a preview image** before finishing. Do not leave a new catalog entry without either a `PreviewImagePath` or an explicit user choice to skip.

## Project numbers

`NodeId` (`PROJ-001`, `PROJ-002`, …) is **assigned automatically** from list order in `BuildCatalog()` via `AssignNodeIds()`. Do **not** set `NodeId` manually when adding entries—append to the list and numbers stay sequential.

## Ask the user

- Whether they have a screenshot/preview for the new project
- Preferred filename (any name under `wwwroot/images/project_thumbnails/`; optional convention `proj-00N.webp` by list position)
- Or an existing path under `wwwroot/images/project_thumbnails/`

If they provide a file, place it in **`wwwroot/images/project_thumbnails/`** (create the folder if missing).

## Wire-up checklist

1. **`ProjectEntry`** — Set `PreviewImagePath` to a site-root path, e.g. `~/images/project_thumbnails/proj-008.webp` (not an absolute filesystem path).
2. **Markup** — [`Pages/Projects.cshtml`](Pages/Projects.cshtml) already renders previews when `PreviewImagePath` is set (between `.proj-desc` and `STACK:`). Do not duplicate markup unless the pattern changes.
3. **Styles** — Use existing `.proj-preview` in [`wwwroot/css/site.css`](wwwroot/css/site.css). Only edit CSS if layout requirements change.
4. **`alt` text** — Uses `{Name} preview` via the shared figure/img block.

## Example

```csharp
// Append to BuildCatalog() — becomes PROJ-006 if it is the 6th entry
new(
    Name: "EXAMPLE APP",
    // ...
    PreviewImagePath: "~/images/project_thumbnails/example-app.webp"
),
```

## Skip only when explicit

If the user says no image yet, leave `PreviewImagePath` null and note they can add the file and path later. Do not invent placeholder images without permission.
